# Git workflow (English only)

**Language:** branch names, commit messages, PR titles, and PR descriptions must always be in **English**.

**Version prefix:** read **`VERSION`** at repo root (e.g. `1.0.0` → use `[1.0]` in PR titles; `2.1.3` → `[2.1]`).

## Agent duty (every completed task)

When finishing work (or when the user may commit/open a PR), **always provide**:

1. Suggested **branch name**
2. Suggested **commit message** (Conventional Commits)
3. Suggested **PR title** — must start with `[M.m]` from `VERSION`
4. Suggested **PR description** — full Markdown body (see template below)

Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks.

## Branch names

Pattern: `{type}/{short-kebab-summary}`

| Type | When |
|------|------|
| `feat/` | New feature or document type |
| `fix/` | Bug fix |
| `docs/` | README, CHANGELOG, VitePress only |
| `chore/` | CI, deps, tooling |
| `test/` | Tests only |

Examples:

- `feat/cpf-generation`
- `fix/cnpj-repeated-digits`
- `docs/packagist-readme`

## Commit messages

[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/), imperative mood, English:

```
<type>(<optional-scope>): <short summary>

<optional body — what and why, not file list>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `refactor`.

Examples:

```
feat(cpf): add check-digit validation for repeated sequences
docs: sync README with Packagist install instructions
chore(ci): run tests on PHP 8.3 and 8.4
```

## PR title

**Required format:**

```
[M.m] <concise title in English>
```

- `[M.m]` = major and minor from `VERSION` (`1.0.0` → `[1.0]`)
- Title: imperative, ~72 chars, no period at end

Examples:

- `[1.0] Add Laravel validation rules for CPF, CNPJ, and CEP`
- `[1.0] Fix CEP repeated-digit rejection`

## PR description (Markdown)

Always output a complete Markdown block the user can paste into GitHub:

```markdown
## Summary

- Bullet 1: what changed
- Bullet 2: why it matters

## Changes

- [ ] Source / API
- [ ] Tests (`composer test`)
- [ ] `README.md`
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` / `VERSION` (if release)
- [ ] Docs `docs/` + `docs/en/` (if user-facing)

## Test plan

- [ ] `composer test`
- [ ] Manual steps if any

## Related

- Closes #issue (if applicable)
```

Adjust checkboxes and sections to match the actual PR.

## Releases

When bumping version, same PR should update `VERSION`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and `README.md`; PR title still uses the **new** `[M.m]` after bump.
